  <section class="content-section" id="section-run-architecture">
    <h2 class="section-heading">
      Run Architecture
      <span class="glossary-tier-badge glossary-tier-badge--intermediate">Intermediate</span>
    </h2>
    <p>
      Above the single-trick level, tricks combine into <strong>runs</strong>:
      ordered sequences of tricks chained through transitions. Run architecture
      is the sequence-level vocabulary that sits on top of the trick-level
      grammar this glossary documents.
    </p>
    <ul class="glossary-run-architecture-topics">
      <li><strong>Combo flow basics</strong> &mdash; how a trick's terminal stall sets up the next trick's entry; the &ldquo;chain language&rdquo; between adjacent tricks.</li>
      <li><strong>Run-quality tiers</strong> (Tiltless, Guiltless, Tripless, Fearless, Beastly, Godly, Genuine, BOP) &mdash; the qualitative ladder for evaluating whole runs.</li>
      <li><strong>Competitive formats</strong> (Routine, Circle, Sick 3, Shred 30) &mdash; the rule sets for competitive freestyle runs.</li>
      <li><strong>Transition patterns</strong> &mdash; common connector-trick choices, e.g. whirl-family tricks acting as central attractors between disparate compounds.</li>
      <li><strong>Density</strong> &mdash; the average ADD per trick across a run; the run-level analogue of per-trick ADD.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="glossary-cross-link">
      Full run-architecture reference (per-tier definitions, format
      specifications, combo-flow analysis, dropless/dropful classification,
      sequence-architecture observations) lives at
      <a href="/freestyle/combo-analysis">Combo Analysis</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

