  {{#if content.connectivePanels.length}}
  <section class="content-section glossary-connective-section" id="connective-panels">
    <h2 class="section-heading">
      Family &amp; Topology Concepts
      <span class="glossary-tier-badge glossary-tier-badge--advanced">Advanced Reference</span>
      <span class="symbolic-layer-badge" title="Observational symbolic-grammar layer — supplementary; does not change canonical classifications">observational</span>
    </h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      Observational <em>movement neighborhoods</em> &mdash; relationship
      browsing for a curator-selected cohort of glossary terms. Each
      panel surfaces how a term lives in practice: tricks that use it,
      related symbolic groups, and (where relevant) operational notation.
      The canonical entries above remain authoritative.
    </p>
    <p class="section-intro detail-muted">
      <strong>This section is intentionally incomplete.</strong> The
      panels below are a <em>representative selection</em>, not a
      comprehensive atlas; the curator will extend coverage as patterns
      stabilize. They describe shared mechanics across tricks but do not
      override the canonical family classifications in the trick
      dictionary.
    </p>
